Privacy Policy

----------------

Introduction  
At The Eagle, we prioritize your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal information. This privacy policy explains how our messaging app, called Messages, operates and ensures the confidentiality of your data. It is important to note that we do not collect any sort of information from our users. By using our Service, you acknowledge and agree to the terms of this policy. The Messages app is provided by The Eagle free of charge and is intended for your convenience.

Information Collection and Use  
We want to reassure you that we do not require or collect any personally identifiable information from you, such as your name, email address, gender, location, or pictures. Our app does not use any third-party services that collect information to identify you. Your privacy is of utmost importance to us.

Cookies  
The Messages app does not utilize cookies explicitly. While we may employ third-party code and libraries, they do not use cookies to collect information or enhance their services. You have the option to accept or refuse cookies from our Service. Please note that if you choose to refuse cookies, certain features of the app may be unavailable to you.

Location Information  
Under no circumstances do we utilize location information transmitted from users' mobile phones. We respect your privacy and do not access or store any location data.

Device Information  
We may collect information from your device to provide a better user experience and prevent fraudulent activity. However, this information does not include any personal identifiers and is used solely for the purpose of improving our services.

Service Providers  
We do not employ any third-party companies or individuals to process or handle your Personal Information. Rest assured that your data remains within the confines of our app and is not shared with any external parties.

Security  
We value your trust in providing us your Personal Information, thus we are striving to use commercially acceptable means of protecting it. But remember that no method of transmission over the internet, or method of electronic storage is 100% secure and reliable, and we cannot guarantee its absolute security.

Privacy of Users  
We understand the importance of your privacy as a user of the Messages app. We are committed to respecting and protecting your personal information. Here are the key points regarding your privacy:

1. Messaging App: The Messages app is designed as a secure messaging platform where users can communicate privately. We respect the privacy of your conversations and do not access, monitor, or store your messages or any other private information exchanged within the app.

2. Access to Private Information: We want to assure you that we do not access or collect any private information from your device or account, including your contacts, photos, or any other personal data. Your private information remains strictly within your control.

3. No Sharing of Private Information: We strictly prohibit the sharing of private information within the Messages app. This includes not disclosing personal details, such as addresses, phone numbers, financial information, or any other sensitive data. We encourage users to exercise caution and discretion when communicating with others.

4. End-to-End Encryption: To ensure the highest level of privacy and security, the Messages app utilizes end-to-end encryption for all communications. This means that only the intended recipients can access and decrypt the messages, ensuring that they remain confidential and protected from unauthorized access.

5. Data Retention: As we do not collect any personal information, we do not retain any user data beyond what is necessary for the functioning of the app. Your messages and other app-related data are stored locally on your device and are not accessible by us.

6. Third-Party Services: The Messages app does not integrate or use any third-party services that may compromise your privacy. We have implemented stringent measures to ensure that your personal information is not shared or accessed by any external parties.

Children's Privacy  
The Messages app is not intended for use by individuals under

 the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal identifiable information from children under 13.
If we become aware that a child under 13 has provided us with personal information, we will promptly delete it from our servers. If you are a parent or guardian and believe that your child has provided us with personal information, please contact us immediately so that we can take necessary action.

Changes to This Privacy Policy  
We reserve the right to update our Privacy Policy as needed. We recommend reviewing this policy periodically for any changes.
We will notify you of any updates by posting the revised Privacy Policy on this page. The changes will be effective immediately upon posting.

Contact Us  
